author: @minxormini1806
text:
Dear Jisoo,

I wanted to take a moment to express my deep appreciation and admiration for you. As a member of the internationally-renowned group Blackpink, you have captured the hearts of millions of fans around the world with your incredible talent and charisma.

Your stunning vocals, dance skills, and stage presence never fail to amaze me. Every time I watch you perform, I am struck by your passion and dedication to your craft. You truly are a gifted artist, and it is clear that you put your heart and soul into everything you do.

But beyond your talent, I am also inspired by your kindness, humility, and grace. You are a role model for so many young people, and your positive influence on your fans cannot be overstated.

author: @Raphael-2
text: When kpop idols perform at music shows, there are fans who attend and they are supposed to cheer with a fanchant. You can hear in all kpop stages from music shows (Music Bank, M Countdown, Music Core, Inkigayo, Show Champion, etc) that there are loud fanchants except during Covid. It's not simple cheering, it is prepared and learned. Usually it's the fanclubs representatives who set the fanchant, but nowadays a lot of idols create the fanchants for the fans and they upload it on YouTube. It is very common. But it's the first time BLACKPINK does this. And I understand it can be very confusing for non kpop fans.
